# Creating Your First Automation

Basic example for automating email sending:

```javascript
// Define the workflow
const emailWorkflow = await client.workflows.create({
  name: 'Welcome Email Sequence',
  trigger: {
    type: 'webhook',
    path: '/user/signup'
  },
  steps: [
    {
      type: 'delay',
      duration: '5m'
    },
    {
      type: 'email',
      template: 'welcome_template',
      to: '{{ user.email }}',
      data: {
        name: '{{ user.name }}',
        company: '{{ user.company }}'
      }
    }
  ]
});

console.log(`Workflow created: ${emailWorkflow.id}`);
```

```python
# Equivalent example in Python
from techflow import TechFlowClient

client = TechFlowClient(api_key=os.getenv('TECHFLOW_API_KEY'))

workflow = client.workflows.create({
    "name": "Welcome Email Sequence",
    "trigger": {
        "type": "webhook",
        "path": "/user/signup"
    },
    "steps": [
        {"type": "delay", "duration": "5m"},
        {
            "type": "email",
            "template": "welcome_template",
            "to": "{{ user.email }}",
            "data": {
                "name": "{{ user.name }}",
                "company": "{{ user.company }}"
            }
        }
    ]
})
```

- Support for JavaScript, Python, PHP, Ruby, and Go
- Templates with {{ }} variable syntax
- Flexible triggers (webhook, cron, events)

