# Error Handling and Retry Logic

Robust implementation with error handling:

```typescript
import { TechFlow, TechFlowError, RetryConfig } from '@techflow/sdk';

const client = new TechFlow({
  apiKey: process.env.TECHFLOW_API_KEY,
  retry: {
    attempts: 3,
    backoff: 'exponential',
    factor: 2
  } as RetryConfig
});

try {
  const result = await client.workflows.execute(workflowId, {
    user: {
      email: 'user@example.com',
      name: 'John Doe'
    }
  });

  console.log('Execution successful:', result.executionId);

} catch (error) {
  if (error instanceof TechFlowError) {
    switch (error.code) {
      case 'RATE_LIMIT_EXCEEDED':
        console.log('Rate limit hit, waiting...');
        await new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, error.retryAfter * 1000));
        break;

      case 'WORKFLOW_NOT_FOUND':
        console.error('Workflow not found:', workflowId);
        break;

      case 'VALIDATION_ERROR':
        console.error('Validation error:', error.details);
        break;

      default:
        console.error('Unknown error:', error.message);
    }
  }
}
```

**Best practices:**
- Always implement exponential retry logic
- Handle each error type specifically
- Log errors for debugging
- Use appropriate timeouts for your use case

