# Webhooks and Real-Time Events

Webhook configuration to receive events:

```javascript
// Configure webhook endpoint
const webhook = await client.webhooks.create({
  url: 'https://your-app.com/webhooks/techflow',
  events: [
    'workflow.completed',
    'workflow.failed',
    'workflow.started'
  ],
  secret: 'your-verification-secret'
});

// Express middleware to handle webhooks
app.post('/webhooks/techflow', express.raw({type: 'application/json'}), (req, res) => {
  const signature = req.headers['x-techflow-signature'];
  const payload = req.body;

  // Verify webhook signature
  if (!client.webhooks.verify(payload, signature, webhook.secret)) {
    return res.status(401).send('Invalid signature');
  }

  const event = JSON.parse(payload);

  switch (event.type) {
    case 'workflow.completed':
      console.log(`Workflow ${event.data.workflowId} completed successfully`);
      break;

    case 'workflow.failed':
      console.error(`Workflow ${event.data.workflowId} failed:`, event.data.error);
      break;

    case 'workflow.started':
      console.log(`Workflow ${event.data.workflowId} started`);
      break;
  }

  res.status(200).send('OK');
});
```

- Mandatory signature verification for security
- Real-time events for reactive integration
- Automatic retry if your endpoint doesn't respond with 200

