# Advanced Conditional Workflows

Creating complex flows with conditional logic:

```javascript
const advancedWorkflow = await client.workflows.create({
  name: 'Smart Lead Nurturing',
  trigger: {
    type: 'webhook',
    path: '/lead/created'
  },
  steps: [
    // Enrich lead data
    {
      type: 'http_request',
      method: 'GET',
      url: 'https://api.clearbit.com/v2/people/find',
      headers: {
        'Authorization': 'Bearer {{ secrets.clearbit_key }}'
      },
      params: {
        email: '{{ lead.email }}'
      },
      output: 'enriched_data'
    },

    // Decision based on company size
    {
      type: 'condition',
      if: '{{ enriched_data.company.metrics.employees > 500 }}',
      then: [
        {
          type: 'assign_to_sales',
          team: 'enterprise',
          priority: 'high'
        },
        {
          type: 'slack_notification',
          channel: '#enterprise-leads',
          message: '🚀 New enterprise lead: {{ lead.name }} from {{ enriched_data.company.name }}'
        }
      ],
      else: [
        {
          type: 'email_sequence',
          template: 'smb_nurturing',
          delay_between: '2d',
          count: 5
        }
      ]
    },

    // Follow-up after 7 days
    {
      type: 'delay',
      duration: '7d'
    },
    {
      type: 'condition',
      if: '{{ lead.status == "not_contacted" }}',
      then: [
        {
          type: 'create_task',
          assignee: '{{ lead.owner }}',
          title: 'Follow up with {{ lead.name }}',
          due_date: 'tomorrow'
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
});
```

**Advanced features:**
- Context variables with {{ }} syntax
- Integration with external APIs
- Complex conditional logic
- Flexible delays and scheduling

